title: Screenshot from 2016-10-28 23-17-28.png
description: thought I just drop this here ... hacking appindicator support for budgie-remix...
comments.comment: Is it a budgie applet for appindicator icons?; It's a c based Canonical app indicator - yes a native budgie applet - not the status notifier app indicator referred to in the budgie desktop TODO list.; +david mohammed are you just loading the .so's directly with GModule?; More conventional... Take ubuntu mate panel applet ... Substitute mate applet code for budgie applet code and you get what you see. Need a cleanup code wise before I will upload it. Slow time.; +david mohammed ah fair enough. FWIW on the coding style I almost always use clang-format now to enforce a strict style on C codebases. That's how the update_format.sh in my repos works (with the accompanying .clang-format)
